g.text: You: "But what's further down the coast?"
You: "Why don't you just do it yourself?"
Logic: You should probably tell Lena. It'll take a load off her mind.
You: "Do you know what caused this wreckage?" (Point at the smashed billboard in the canal.)
Man on water lock: "I wasn't here to witness it, but those look like tyre tracks on that sign. Weird, huh? Then again, plenty of daredevil drivers in Revachol."
Man on water lock: Variable["TASK.close_water_lock_done"] or Variable["canal.water_lock_alt_cant_chat"]
Man on water lock: "High time I got moving up the coast. But please, officer, after you."
"'Fraid I can't hang out and chat." He looks west, across the water. "High time I got moving up the coast. But, please, officer, after you."
Man on water lock: "'Fraid I can't hang out and chat." He looks west, across the water, chewing on a piece of salami. "Damned water lock's finally been fixed, so I've got to get going."
Man on water lock: "Good morning to you, officer!"

Man on water lock: "Well, there's the fishing village. An abandoned fish market. A bizarro church. Not much use to the congregation, though -- there always seems to be something wrong with it." He thinks for a moment.
Man on water lock: "Welcome back, officer."
Man on water lock: "Bah! I've handled enough heavy machinery in my day."
Man on water lock: "So, wanna do the honours now?"
Man on water lock: "Have you ever made a water lock move yourself?" he adds, gesturing toward the water lock control panel to his right. "It's quite the thing. Makes a man feel real powerful."
Man on water lock: "Sure thing." He cuts off a slice of salami.
Perception (Taste): It is salty. It is savoury. It is chewy. The hangover only makes the salami *more* tasty.
Man on water lock: "Suit yourself. Just drop by on Wednesday if you want to see the water lock work again." He cuts a fresh slice from his salami.
You: "But, wait, what's further down the coast?"

Man on water lock: "Well, there's the fishing village. An abandoned fish market. A bizarro church. Not much use to the congregation, though -- there always seems to be something wrong with it." He thinks for a moment.
Inland Empire: The words *daredevil driver* sound ominous to you.
You: "Do you know what's further down the coast?"

Man on water lock: "Well, there's the fishing village. An abandoned fish market. A bizarro church. Not much use to the congregation, though -- there always seems to be something wrong with it." He thinks for a moment.
Man on water lock: "Want some too, officer?" he turns to the lieutenant.
Man on water lock: "My friend Barry the Butcher is stuck on the other side of the water lock. I'm keeping him company -- and eating his salami."

Barry the Butcher: From the corner of your eye you see a man in a yellow shirt and grey overalls waving at you from across the canal. He seems disappointed about the wreckage on the water lock -- *and* the salami.
You: "You said the coast is closed off? This may be why Lena's husband Morell the cryptozoologist hasn't returned."
Man on water lock: "Uhm... I haven't seen any *cryptologists* around here, but sure -- if they're on the other side, they're stuck. Like my friend Barry."
You: "Can I have some of that salami?" (Point at his food.)
Man on water lock: "*Very* good stuff. Anything I can do for you, officer?" The man on the water lock picks the skin off a slice of a salami and takes a sizeable bite.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Why not?" The lieutenant ponders the offer for a moment, then decides to go for it. He takes a slice of salami from the man and chews on it.
Man on water lock: "G'day to you, officer!"
You: "What's with the lever that does nothing?" (Point at the control panel next to him.)
Man on water lock: "It's supposed to operate the water lock, but as noted... it's all junk right now. Disabled because of the blockage."
Man on water lock: "Yeah, not really much else. Just bombed-out ruins."
Composure: He doesn't actually seem to be in a rush. It's not in his nature. Enviable calm.
You: "First things first -- what are you doing here, man on the water lock?"
Man on water lock: "Great! Just drop in on Wednesday if you want to see the water lock at work. They say the canal crew will be here at 07.15." He cuts a fresh slice from his salami.
Man on water lock: "Cheers!" He salutes you with a half-eaten piece of salami.
Man on water lock: "Yeah, not really much else. Just bombed-out ruins."
Man on water lock: "G'day to you, officer!"
You: "We'll see... I'm not all that into manual labour."

Man on water lock: A burly man hangs out by the water lock, carving up a generous serving of salami with an old hunter's knife. His eyes are fixed on a man stranded on the other side of the water lock -- and on an enormous billboard that has fallen down into the canal between them.
Man on water lock: "Good morning to you, officer!"
Man on water lock: "It'll be restarted on Wednesday morning." He nods his head towards the control panel. "You wanna do the honours when the time comes?"
Man on water lock: "Safety measure. Turns out the panel needs a special key to be re-activated. Wouldn't want anyone moving the water lock with debris still in the channel."
Reaction Speed: This is the water lock on the Martinaise Canal. It has to be the same water lock Lena mentioned, the one her husband crossed on his "expedition."
Physical Instrument: His posture is relaxed. Despite his powerful build and the knife in his hand, this man resorts to physical intimidation only infrequently, if at all.
Man on water lock: "Too bad it also takes a year and a day to repair anything 'round here -- especially a water lock. The rest of the coast is closed off till then."
Man on water lock: Variable["whirling.lena_husband_across_water_lock"] and Variable["canal.know_water_lock_time"] == false
Man on water lock: "Yeah, not really much else. Just bombed-out ruins."
Kim Kitsuragi: "We should probably go tell Lena. Take a load off her mind."
Tutorial Agent: The coast part of the map is inaccessible until the third day.
